  "sbox_derivation": "AES S-box. Normative definition is the 256-byte table above; the production path computes it constant-time via the bitsliced Boyar-Peralta circuit (no secret-indexed lookup) and is byte-identical to the table. DRAFT constants carry no security claim.",
  "sbox_circuit": {
    "type": "boyar-peralta-forward-aes",
    "reference": "Boyar & Peralta, A small depth-16 circuit for the AES S-box, IACR ePrint 2011/332, Figs 5/7/8",
    "and_gates": 34,
    "bitslice": "orthogonalize the 64 state bytes into 8 bit-planes (per-word 8x8 transpose), one circuit pass over u64 lanes, scatter back; constant-time, table-free",
    "verification": "reproduces this table for all 256 inputs: sah-research/scripts/bitslice_sbox_check.py plus exhaustive Zig and Rust unit tests; bound across tracks by the KAT vectors"
  },
